## ORM (Odoo 15 — diverges from 12/13)

- Methods are **recordset by default**. `@api.multi` was removed in 14 and stays removed in 15 — do not import or apply it.
- `@api.model` for class-level methods that don't need a recordset.
- `@api.model_create_multi` to override `create()`. A single-record `@api.model` `create()` override silently breaks batch create.
- `@api.depends`, `@api.constrains`, `@api.onchange`, `@api.depends_context` behave as in 14.
- Call `ensure_one()` when a method assumes one record.
- Parameterised SQL only. Batch `write()` and `unlink()`.
- Document every `sudo()` with a one-line reason in code.
- Prefer ORM over SQL. When SQL writes are unavoidable, invalidate or refresh affected caches.
- `_check_company_auto` exists but is not the project default in 15 — only enable it when the model explicitly needs multi-company auto-check.

## Performance

- No `search()` / `browse(id)` inside loops.
- Prefer `read_group(..., lazy=False)` for grouped counts and sums.
- Push filtering into domains; do not filter in Python after a broad search.
- Use `search_count()` instead of `len(search())`.
- Batch recordset work with `mapped`, `filtered`, grouped domains, set operations.
- Keep computed fields prefetch-friendly; declare a complete `@api.depends`.
- Store computed fields only when they are searched, grouped, sorted, or repeatedly displayed at scale.

## Views and models

- Inheritance edits use `<xpath>` with `position="after|before|inside|replace|attributes"`.
- View conditions in 15 still accept **both** styles: `attrs="{'invisible': [...]}"` / `states="..."` AND inline Python `invisible="<expr>"`. Both are valid in 15; `attrs` / `states` are deprecated in 16 and removed in 17 — avoid only when the file is already being migrated.
- New widget types available in 15: `widget="domain"`, `widget="json_editor"`, etc. Prefer them over hand-rolled inputs when present.
- Keep XML IDs stable across releases.
- Use `_sql_constraints` or `@api.constrains` for validation.

## Frontend (the v15 pitfall)

- **OWL v1 is the default for new components.** Web client is increasingly OWL but still ships QWeb/jQuery legacy in some places.
- **Legacy kanban JS framework was removed in 15.** Old kanban widgets that depended on it must be migrated to OWL or to the supported kanban widget set — do not delete them blindly, audit usages first.
- Existing QWeb / jQuery widgets continue to work. Do **not** rewrite them wholesale unless the task explicitly asks.
- New JS components go under `static/src/` as OWL modules with `t-*` directives.
- Do not introduce new jQuery selectors for new code paths.

## Security and style

- Keep `ir.model.access.csv` and `ir.rule` aligned with new models.
- Raise `UserError` for business rules, `ValidationError` for invalid data.
- Use `_logger`, never `print()`.
- Imports order: stdlib, third-party, `odoo`, local — in that order.
- Respect multi-company and record rules unless the task explicitly requires privileged behaviour.
- `mail` framework in 15 is still v1 — chatter inheritance and message_post APIs follow the pre-v2 contract.

## Verification

- Module install/update: `{{PYTHON_BIN}} odoo-bin -u <module> --stop-after-init -d {{DEFAULT_DB}}`.
- Module tests: `--test-enable --test-tags /<module> --stop-after-init`.
- For algorithm correctness against real data, prefer `realdata_test.eval_orm_expression` and `consistency_check_eval` over UI-driven repro.
- PostgreSQL ≥ 12 is required for 15; older clusters fail at registry boot.
